{"title":"Wand of light","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Wand_of_light","type":"markdown","data":"| /               |                                                               |\n| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name            | light                                                         |\n| Appearance      | [random](/wiki/Randomised_appearance \"Randomised appearance\") |\n| Abundance       | [9.5%](/wiki/Wand#Generation \"Wand\")                          |\n| Base price      | 100 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\")                             |\n| Weight          | 7                                                             |\n| Type            | non-directional                                               |\n| Maximum charges | 15                                                            |\n| Spell           | [light](/wiki/Spellbook_of_light \"Spellbook of light\")        |\n| Monster use     | *Will not be used by monsters.*                               |\n\nThe **wand of light** is a [wand](/wiki/Wand \"Wand\") that appears in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Generation](#Generation)\n- [2 Effects](#Effects)\n- [3 Strategy](#Strategy)\n- [4 Variants](#Variants)\n  - [4.1 Sporkhack](#Sporkhack)\n\n## Generation\n\nThere is a 9.5% chance that a randomly-generated wand will be a wand of light, making it the most commonly generated wand.\n\n## Effects\n\nWhen zapped or engraved with, the wand [lights](/wiki/Light \"Light\") an area with radius of 5, or the whole room if on the [Rogue level](/wiki/Rogue_level \"Rogue level\").\n\n...xxxxx...  \n..xxxxxxx..  \n.xxxxxxxxx.  \nxxxxxxxxxxx  \nxxxxxxxxxxx  \nxxxxx\\@xxxxx  \nxxxxxxxxxxx  \nxxxxxxxxxxx  \n.xxxxxxxxx.  \n..xxxxxxx..  \n...xxxxx...\n\nLike other wands, [applying](/wiki/Apply \"Apply\") a wand of light will break it, resulting in an explosion dealing 1 to (4*n*) damage, with the hero being blinded for (*n*+1)d25 turns, with *n* being the number of remaining charges. The same area is lit as when the wand is zapped; surrounding monsters may also be blinded, and [gremlins](/wiki/Gremlin \"Gremlin\") take damage.\n\n## Strategy\n\nIn the early game, a wand of light may be useful to help mapping unlit floors of the [Gnomish Mines](/wiki/Gnomish_Mines \"Gnomish Mines\"). Certain [quest](/wiki/Quest \"Quest\") levels also have large unlit sections, where it may be useful to mark where the player has been (though there is an option to make this redundant). It can also aid in [jumping](/wiki/Jumping \"Jumping\") to get away from dangerous situations if you have no [lamp](/wiki/Lamp \"Lamp\").\n\nSome players use a wand of light to mark the location of the [Vibrating square](/wiki/Vibrating_square \"Vibrating square\") and light paths between staircases in Gehennom; this will be a great help if you happen to [get](/wiki/Mind_flayer \"Mind flayer\") [amnesia](/wiki/Scroll_of_amnesia \"Scroll of amnesia\"), but is probably not worth the effort in most cases.\n\nOnce you obtain and can reliably cast the [light](/wiki/Spellbook_of_light \"Spellbook of light\") spell, the wand of light becomes practically useless unless you are constantly low on [energy](/wiki/Energy \"Energy\"), and is superseded by the spell for all of the above usages. The wand is good [polyfodder](/wiki/Polyfodder \"Polyfodder\") at this point, as it is usually generated with a lot of charges.\n\n## Variants\n\n### Sporkhack\n\nIn [Sporkhack](/wiki/Sporkhack \"Sporkhack\"), wands of light blind nearby creatures when engraving or zapping with them. Be wary of using them close to [aligned priests](/wiki/Aligned_priests \"Aligned priests\") or the [Minetown](/wiki/Minetown \"Minetown\") [watch](/wiki/Watch \"Watch\").\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.](/images/5/57/Nh366-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Wand of light - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Wand_of_light\",\"wgTitle\":\"Wand of light\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":136406,\"wgRevisionId\":136406,\"wgArticleId\":2181,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Wands\",\"Nethack-366 articles\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Wand_of_light\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":2181,\"wgRequestId\":\"5f1934951169cb7c77ab530a\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.toc.s